This is a good direction because “stasis” isn’t just one concept. Biology, medicine, psychology, and systems theory use a whole family of -stasis ideas, each preserving something different.

Here’s how I’d organize them through the Pantheon lens.

Stasis	What is Preserved?	Pantheon Interpretation
Homeostasis	Internal state	Keep the core stable.
Allostasis	Functional performance	Change to stay effective.
Hemostasis	Blood integrity	Stop leaks; preserve the system after damage.
Thermostasis	Temperature	Maintain operating conditions.
Osmostasis	Water/solute balance	Balance exchange across boundaries.
Electrostatic equilibrium	Charge balance	Prevent runaway accumulation.
Proteostasis	Protein quality	Repair, recycle, and replace damaged components.
Immunostasis	Immune balance	Defend without attacking yourself.
Redox homeostasis	Oxidation balance	Manage energy and damage.
Metabolic homeostasis	Energy availability	Allocate resources efficiently.

